cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the use of Richardson extrapolation in machine learning, specifically in optimization algorithms and regularization techniques. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The applications to computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS) are also possible, as the techniques discussed in the paper could be applied to problems in these areas.
